    • Method Detail

      • createDataTable

        void createDataTable()
              throws java.sql.SQLException,
                     java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        This function fills myData with arrays. Each array represents a entry from the database where each entry is loaded into an array index. The resulting array is then used in the JTable to fill its contents with the database entries.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - thrown if connection to SQL server failed
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - thrown is classpath is broken

      • createGroupDisplay

        javax.swing.JPanel createGroupDisplay(UserView view)
        Creates a JPanel that shows the groups that are currently in the database. The panel is updated as groups are added and deleted.
        Parameters:
        view - The current JFrame for AdminView
        Returns:
        The Panel that displays the groups

      • updateGroups

        Parameters:
        view - The current JFrame for AdminView

      • removeGroup

        private void removeGroup(UserView view)
                  throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException,
                         java.sql.SQLException
        This function removes a group from the database. It brings up a JDialog if the admin presses the delete group button, but has not selected a group to delete.
        Parameters:
        view - The current JFrame used for AdminView
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - thrown is classpath is broken
        java.sql.SQLException - thrown if error connection to SQL server

      • resetData

        protected void resetData()
        Updates the default table model, and is called by functions in the DataController. This happens when a new entry is made, edited, or deleted, and the table properly reflects the changes made by the user.
